&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a detail-oriented professional with deep experience in legal technology and process improvement? If so, Democracy Forward Foundation (“Democracy Forward”) is looking for a Legal Technology and Operations Manager to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Legal Technology and Operations Manager will play an instrumental role in ensuring the effective and efficient work of the Legal Team, which includes our litigators and legal support team of paralegals and legal assistants. The Legal Team has an exceptionally fast-paced and growing litigation docket and regularly files on tight timelines. This position is responsible for understanding the Legal Team’s technological needs and workflows, helping the team use the platforms it has, recommending and testing additional platforms and applications, and assisting the team with filings and discovery when necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Legal Team uses several technology platforms&amp;nbsp; (&lt;em&gt;e.g.&lt;/em&gt;, Westlaw, Logikcull, Orbital, CourtDrive, Sharepoint, Word, Adobe, CourtDrive, Google suite, AirTable, Permacc, PACER, CM-ECF)). This Legal Technology and Operations Manager is responsible for recommending workflows for these platforms given the team’s needs and platform capability, and then implementing and trouble shooting those workflows so the Legal Team can use the platforms with minimum disruption. This position would also be the primary liaison with our current vendors, and explore new platforms and applications that meet the Legal Team’s needs and workflows. The position is also responsible for assisting in the maintenance of accurate data and files so that reports can be accurately and easily created. On occasion, the Legal Technology and Operations Manager may be asked to support filings and discovery productions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is full time and may require evening and weekend work when there are time-sensitive filings or problems that need to be fixed. Democracy Forward’s office is located in Washington, DC. While this position offers flexibility to work remotely, it requires regular in-office presence eight (8) times per month (averaging 2 times per week) to effectively support the Legal Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Legal Technology and Operations Manager will report to the Managing Attorney and work closely with the Deputy Managing Attorneys and will support other members of the Legal Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Below are the key areas of responsibility for this role. The specifics of each responsibility may vary based on the needs of the organization and department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Information Technology:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based on the Legal Team’s workflow and needs, provide expertise and assistance on existing Legal Team technology and platforms so that the Legal Team gets the maximum utility from these platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the Legal Team&#39;s dedicated liaison to the organization&#39;s IT team, building and maintaining a strong collaborative relationship to ensure the Legal Team&#39;s needs are effectively met across enterprise-wide systems, infrastructure changes, and technology initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify skills gaps and recommend and create/coordinate training for the Legal Team on existing platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate the Legal Team’s use of technology and platforms and recommend improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and recommend cost-efficient new legal platforms and technology for use by the Legal Team that will increase the Team’s efficiency and improve its recordkeeping, organization, and efficacy while fitting with its workflow and priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
