&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a mission-driven researcher with a passion for defending democratic institutions and tracking the forces working to undermine them? If so, Democracy Forward Foundation (&quot;Democracy Forward&quot;) is looking for a Research Assistant to join its Strategic Initiatives team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Democracy Forward seeks a highly collaborative researcher to join its team of litigators and policy professionals to help track and assess the activities of the right-wing legal movement and coordinated efforts to undermine liberal democracy in the United States. The Research Assistant will help drive Democracy Forward’s research and data collection on right wing legal organizations, attempts to undermine or eliminate DEIA policies and practices, and efforts to advance anti-democratic law and policy. The role will identify and track these trends, help maintain and develop Democracy Forward’s data systems, work across the organization to develop timely and insightful analysis, and support Democracy Forward’s collaboration with key stakeholders and partners outside the organization to turn data into action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is full-time. Democracy Forward’s office is located in Washington, DC. While this position offers flexibility to work remotely, it requires regular in-office presence eight (8) times per month (averaging 2 times per week). Remote candidates within the United States will also be considered. If a candidate is outside of the DC area, travel to DC is expected 1–2 times per quarter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The application deadline for this role is July 23, 2026 at 11:59pm ET.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Below are the key areas of responsibility for this role. The specifics of each responsibility may vary based on the needs of the organization and department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support efforts to track, analyze, and report on the organization and litigation strategies of the right-wing legal movement and its efforts to undermine democratic institutions and the rule of law.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with policy and research staff to maintain timely, accurate, and robust information about these and other legal and policy trends across a range of progressive issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with all teams across the organization to develop useful analyses and synthesis of data on emerging threats to liberal democracy, including litigation trends, personnel networks, and coordinated policy campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay abreast of current events and the legal and policy landscape related to anti-democratic activities in the United States, including the activities of right-wing legal organizations, dark money funders, and state-level actors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare briefings for internal staff as well as external stakeholders, such as partner organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support efforts to collaborate and develop partnerships that enhance and strengthen Democracy Forward’s impact, including those seeking to understand and counter threats in the legal and policy landscape&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We recognize that strong candidates may not meet 100% of the qualifications listed. If you believe you can contribute meaningfully to our team, we encourage you to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For Research Assistant: 0-2 years of experience working in research, policy, or legal environments and/or organizations that work at the intersection of government, law, and policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For Research Analyst: 3+ years of experience working in research, policy, or legal environments and/or organizations that work at the intersection of government, law, and policy&lt;/li

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Democracy Forward Foundation (“Democracy Forward”) is seeking multiple full-time&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;Litigation Paralegals and Senior Litigation Paralegals to carry out its mission to promote pro-democracy and progressive policies and ideals via litigation and regulatory engagement. These individuals will serve as an integral part of litigation case teams and ensure that case filings are produced in a timely and professional manner. These positions are part of the Legal Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidates will have experience working independently and with a team to draft, analyze, and prepare legal documents for a supervising lawyer or supervising paralegal and collecting, evaluating, and summarizing relevant facts and legal concepts for a supervising lawyer or supervising paralegal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is full-time. Democracy Forward’s office is located in Washington, DC. While this position offers flexibility to work remotely, it requires regular in-office presence eight (8) times per month (averaging 2 times per week) to effectively support the nature of the role. Remote candidates within the United States will also be considered. If a candidate is outside of the DC area, travel to DC is expected 1-2 times per quarter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Litigation Paralegal / Senior Litigation Paralegal will report to the Managing Attorney, and work with the entire Legal team including other Paralegals, Legal Assistants, and attorneys.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Below are the key areas of responsibility for this role. The specifics of each responsibility may vary based on the needs of the organization and department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform cite-checking, blue-booking, proofreading, and formatting for motions, briefs, complaints, and legal filings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use legal software, such as for e-discovery, PDFs, word processing, table of authorities, legal research, case search, and case management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Understand and follow litigation practice area protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize case documents, including following established systems and protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review documents for relevance, responsiveness, and privileged and confidential information, and prepare documents for production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in hearing or trial preparation and logistics, including management of scheduling, coordination with court clerks, preparation of digital and hard-copy document collections, and in-court logistics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare pleadings and discovery under lawyer supervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;File and e-file pleadings in federal, state courts and government agencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We recognize that strong candidates may not meet 100% of the qualifications listed. If you believe you can contribute meaningfully to our team, we encourage you to apply.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For Litigation Paralegal: 5 or more years of legal support experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For Senior Litigation Paralegal: 10 or more years of legal support experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant experience substantively cite-checking, BlueBooking, formatting, and proofreading legal filings and supporting documents, including complaints, requests for preliminary relief, and dispositive motions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant experience using software programs and applications, such as for e-discovery, PDFs, word processing, table of authorities, table of contents, legal research, docket searches, case searches, and case and file management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience organizing and preparing documents and exhibits for filing, including use of Adobe PDF and CM-ECF/PACER

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a mission-driven professional with experience supporting the travel and advance of executive principals? If so, Democracy Forward Foundation (“Democracy Forward”) is looking for a Travel and Advance Manager to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly organized and collaborative Travel and Advance Manager that will play a pivotal role in the planning and execution of the President and CEO’s travel and public engagements. This position will be responsible for ensuring that the Principal’s travels and events run smoothly, efficiently, and align with organizational objectives. The position will occasionally support the planning and execution of travel needs for senior executives. The role is central to ensuring that public events and advance operations are consistent across all types of engagements and that staff and stakeholders are well prepared to execute successful events.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is full-time. Democracy Forward’s office is located in Washington, DC. Candidates based in the DC area and remote within the United States will be considered, with travel being expected up to 80% of the time.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Travel and Advance Manager will report to the Director of Executive Scheduling and work closely with the Executive Office and external partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We encourage early applications, as they will be reviewed on a rolling basis starting July 10, 2026.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
