&lt;p&gt;Below are the key areas of responsibility for this role. The specifics of each responsibility may vary based on the needs of the organization and department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel Planning&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working closely with Executive Office (EO) team members, coordinating on all aspects of the Principal’s domestic and international travel, including flights, hotels, and ground transportation, ensuring compliance with organizational travel policies. This may also include some travel planning for other senior executives within the EO.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the Director of Scheduling to develop detailed trip itineraries for all of the Principal’s travel.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively address travel disruptions and operational challenges to minimize impact on the Principal&#39;s schedule and objectives. This may also include addressing disruptions to senior executives’ travel as necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the Director of Executive Scheduling with planning for security needs for the Principal’s travel and events.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide regular updates on the Principal’s upcoming travel to internal teams to support stakeholder outreach and identification of strategic engagement opportunities involving existing and prospective donors, partners, and organizational allies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain comprehensive travel records, expense documentation, and engagement details to support the preparation of executive trip reports.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
